v2.5.4 (July 5th 2026)

- Fixed Kohya SDXL training startup against the shared core Transformers 5.x stack by making the launcher compatibility check require both `Dinov2WithRegistersConfig` and Kohya's still-used `CLIPFeatureExtractor` alias before it accepts the installed `transformers` package.
- Preserved the existing `KOHYA_TRANSFORMERS_VERSION=4.57.6` runtime self-repair path so existing images downgrade the shared core Transformers package for Kohya instead of failing with `ImportError: cannot import name 'CLIPFeatureExtractor'`.
- Added a regression check so both Kohya launch entrypoints keep the CLIP/DINO compatibility probe in sync.

v2.5.3 (July 3rd 2026)

- Made TensorBoard integration actually functional for training stacks that mattered, not just eyecandy:
  - added shared status endpoint `GET /api/tensorboard/status`
  - trained-stack discovery now checks `events.out.tfevents.*` for Diffusion Pipe, TrainPilot, Kohya, and AI Toolkit
  - added shared TensorBoard source links under `/workspace/logs/tensorboard/{diffpipe,trainpilot,kohya,ai-toolkit}` in Diffusion Pipe launcher
- Wired TensorBoard actions into UI entry points:
  - TrainPilot and Diffusion Pipe pages now include open/status actions
  - Services page now exposes a TensorBoard action for diffpipe/kohya/AI Toolkit with run-state aware status text
- Updated docs for workflow visibility (`training-workflows`, stack component docs, API reference) and added release notes.

v2.5.2 (July 3rd 2026)

- Bumped VS Code in-browser service to code-server `4.127.0` and JupyterLab to `4.6.1` in the canonical build configuration.
- Updated build-time pin surfaces (`Dockerfile`, `Makefile`, `build.env.example`, and build docs) so the same tool versions are used for every image build path.

v2.5.1 (July 3rd 2026)

- Updated TagPilot to the latest frontend behavior set, including restored dataset loading via ControlPilot’s `?dataset=` integration, saved workspace export action, and embedded dark-mode sync.
- Restored TagPilot’s save-to-workspace dataset flow so datasets can be opened from ControlPilot and edited with existing tags in place.
- Hardened TagPilot and training path handling: dataset names are validated, and dataset/model filesystem paths are canonicalized with explicit realpath checks before use.
- Hardened model pull input handling on backend-triggered flows to reduce path/command risk exposure flagged by security scans.

v2.5.0 (June 12th 2026)

- Added dual CUDA build profiles: `CUDA_PROFILE=cu130` is now the default Blackwell path on CUDA `13.0.2` with PyTorch `2.12.0`, while `CUDA_PROFILE=cu128` keeps the legacy CUDA `12.8.1` path with PyTorch `2.11.0`.
- Made `torchaudio` optional for the CUDA 13.0 profile because the matching official `cu130` wheel is not currently available.
- Consolidated runtime Python environments from five venvs to three: `/opt/venvs/core` now owns the shared GPU stack plus JupyterLab, Diffusion Pipe, and TensorBoard; `/opt/venvs/invoke` and `/opt/venvs/ai-toolkit` keep local package isolation while importing the core GPU stack.
- Refreshed major build pins: ComfyUI `v0.24.1`, InvokeAI `6.13.0`, JupyterLab `4.5.8`, code-server `4.123.0`, Diffusion Pipe `5aa6577`, AI Toolkit `8812755`, xFormers `0.0.35`, Diffusers `0.38.0`, Transformers `5.11.0`, Accelerate `1.14.0`, PEFT `0.19.1`, Hugging Face Hub `1.19.0`, and bitsandbytes `0.49.2`.
- Pinned npm to `11.17.0` for the AI Toolkit UI build/runtime path and patched AI Toolkit's deprecated Next dev indicator config out of the bundled UI.
- Suppressed Kohya's upstream `pkg_resources` deprecation warning without doing runtime setuptools repairs during service startup.
- Suppressed TensorBoard's `pkg_resources` deprecation warning in the Diffusion Pipe launcher readiness check and both TensorBoard start paths.
- Refreshed `models.manifest` so the image default and repo reference manifest stay aligned, and added Comfy-ready quantized Ideogram 4, Lens, and PixelDiT entries without duplicating the shared `flux2-vae` entry.
- Preserved TagPilot provider key clearing in the UI and the bootstrap secret rewrite behavior for `HF_TOKEN`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `GEMINI_API_KEY`, and `XAI_API_KEY`.

v2.4.3 (May 7th 2026)

- Fixed TagPilot cloud-provider image uploads by normalizing/inferring image MIME types before calling OpenAI, Gemini, and Grok. JPEG/PNG/WebP/etc. no longer arrive upstream as useless `application/octet-stream`, truly a concept humanity should have retired already.
- Updated Gemini generation to try stable `v1` first with a `v1beta` fallback, and updated Grok generation to prefer xAI Responses API with chat-completions fallback.
- Changed TagPilot provider failures to return JSON `424` responses instead of gateway-style `502` responses, preventing RunPod/Cloudflare from replacing useful provider errors with their HTML lecture.
- Made TagPilot provider keys persist to `/workspace/config/secrets.env` and preserved those saved keys across bootstrap secret rewrites.
- Added `/opt/pilot/tagpilot-provider-smoke.py` for live OpenAI/Gemini/Grok compatibility checks against the current provider APIs.
- Fixed TagPilot dark-mode startup and added a crop quick-action button to the image preview modal.
- Reworked Dockerfile service install layers for cacheable rebuilds, fixed optional install shell conditionals, and kept runtime finalization after runtime scripts are copied.

v2.4.2 (May 6th 2026)

- Upgraded the Blackwell-focused build baseline to CUDA `12.8.1` with core `torch==2.8.0`, `torchvision==0.23.0`, `torchaudio==2.8.0`, `xformers==0.0.32.post2`, and `bitsandbytes==0.49.2`.
- Refreshed bundled service refs/pins: ComfyUI `v0.20.2`, ComfyUI-Manager `4.2.1`, Kohya `v25.2.1`, InvokeAI `6.12.0`, AI Toolkit `6bb8acb`, and Diffusion Pipe `535bc58`.
- Split AI Toolkit into its own `/opt/venvs/ai-toolkit` environment so its newer Transformers/Diffusers stack no longer fights InvokeAI. Tiny mercy, big payoff.
- Moved TagPilot Gemini/Grok/OpenAI generation through ControlPilot backend endpoints and persisted provider keys in `/workspace/config/secrets.env` instead of browser-side storage.
- Added TagPilot provider APIs: `GET /api/tagpilot/providers`, `POST /api/tagpilot/providers/{provider}/key`, and `POST /api/tagpilot/generate`.

v2.4.1 (April 6th 2026)

- Cleared the GitHub CodeQL/code-scanning findings by hardening ControlPilot, MediaPilot, Portal JS, and the Copilot sidecar around path handling, process launch inputs, secret storage, exception exposure, and client-side URL/DOM handling.
- Retired the legacy `apps/Portal/dpipe-gui.py` Gradio entrypoint and replaced it with a deprecation stub in favor of the active ControlPilot Diffusion Pipe UI/API path.
- Upgraded the shared core GPU stack to `torch==2.7.0+cu128`, `torchvision==0.22.0+cu128`, `torchaudio==2.7.0+cu128`, switched the core wheel index to `cu128`, and relaxed xFormers to `>=0.0.30` for Blackwell testing.

v2.4 (March 27th 2026)

- Added a real `Settings` section in ControlPilot with optional password protection, persisted sessions, and centralized management for HF, Copilot, MediaPilot, and Jupyter secrets plus shutdown and UI defaults.
- Moved Settings directly under Dashboard, gave it a distinct sidebar icon, and kept light/dark toggle access in the primary menu.
- Removed Copilot from the primary nav and kept it as a global drawer with better layout, browser-first token setup, and inline auth guidance.
- Disabled misleading in-app updates for git-managed services; ComfyUI, Kohya, Diffusion Pipe, and AI Toolkit are now treated as image-managed.
- Cleaned up embedded app layouts: MediaPilot now uses the full content area, its light-mode icons were fixed, and workspace sync became content-aware so UI asset updates propagate to existing pods.
- Simplified the ComfyUI page by removing the hero chrome, removing the iframe frame, and adding a collapsible live-preview side panel.
- Made TrainPilot TOML editing persistent on `/workspace`, added validation, limited log scanning to TrainPilot/Kohya logs, and sped up dataset listing/population for larger collections.
- Wired TrainPilot Kohya runs into TensorBoard on port `4444` and tightened TrainPilot/Dpipe form sizing on desktop.
- Fixed dataset tag detection so tagged datasets no longer show up as `No tags`.
- Hardened the Kohya training stack by bumping core `transformers` to `4.48.3`, adding startup self-repair for older images, and pinning Kohya/Diffusion Pipe refs.
- Isolated Diffusion Pipe into its own venv, tightened Invoke/AI Toolkit shared dependency constraints, and hardened the Diffusion Pipe/TensorBoard launcher path.
- Fixed code-server secret handling so runtime auth matches `/workspace/config/secrets.env`, and cleaned up the startup banner.
- Refactored the Docker build by extracting major install/setup blocks into `scripts/build/*`, centralizing git checkout, constraints, venv bootstrap, patching, and final runtime normalization.
- Removed `apt-get upgrade` from the image build and reduced repetitive top-level script copy instructions.

